{"title":"The 2024 Marin Four Corners 1 Retails for $999","link":"https://theradavist.com/2024-marin-four-corners-1/","date":1705677402000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2429\" height=\"1619\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?fit=1200,1619&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?w=2429&amp;quality=75 2429w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?resize=2000,1333&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1.jpg?resize=2048,1365&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p>In the style of the Kona Sutra ULTD, AWOL, Bombtrack Beyond 2, Stargazer, and others, the <a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/bikes/2024-four-corners\" target=\"_blank\">2024 Marin Four Corners 1</a> ($999) is a touring bike in its DNA but can be used for a number of different activities from gravel riding to commuting.<span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2649\" height=\"1815\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?fit=1200,1815&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?w=2649&amp;quality=75 2649w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?resize=1200,822&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?resize=2000,1370&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?resize=768,526&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?resize=1536,1052&amp;quality=75 1536w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/01/2024MarinFourCorners1_2.jpeg?resize=2048,1403&amp;quality=75 2048w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Marin designed the Four Corners 1 to have five different frame sizes, with size-matched 650b or 700C wheels to fit riders between 4’11” – 6’4”.</em> </p>\n<p>A butted 4130 CrMo steel frame and fork are designed to be comfortable on rough roads but to also handle fully loaded touring. The Four Corners 1 includes six bottle mounts, rack and fender eyelets, lowrider fork mounts, generous tire clearance and disc brakes to set you up for all conditions and all terrain. All at a $999 price tag.</p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/bikes/2024-four-corners\" target=\"_blank\">Marin Bikes</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2024-marin-four-corners-1/\">The 2024 Marin Four Corners 1 Retails for $999</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"637e15c00c4543ace9b3d22ab980c0cc1d8aae5131ac79768a0fddc74e2db149","category":"Cycling"}